37#define LOOP_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('L','O','O','P')
38
39isc_result_t
40cfg_aclconfctx_create(isc_mem_t *mctx, cfg_aclconfctx_t **ret) {
41 cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx;
42
43 REQUIRE(mctx != NULL);
44 REQUIRE(ret != NULL && *ret == NULL);
45
46 actx = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(*actx));
47 if (actx == NULL)
48 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
49
50 isc_refcount_init(&actx->references, 1);
51
52 actx->mctx = NULL;
53 isc_mem_attach(mctx, &actx->mctx);
54 ISC_LIST_INIT(actx->named_acl_cache);
55
56#ifdef HAVE_GEOIP
57 actx->geoip = NULL;
58#endif
59
60 *ret = actx;
61 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
62}
63
64void
65cfg_aclconfctx_attach(cfg_aclconfctx_t *src, cfg_aclconfctx_t **dest) {
66 REQUIRE(src != NULL);
67 REQUIRE(dest != NULL && *dest == NULL);
68
69 isc_refcount_increment(&src->references);
70 *dest = src;
71}
72
73void
74cfg_aclconfctx_detach(cfg_aclconfctx_t **actxp) {
75 REQUIRE(actxp != NULL && *actxp != NULL);
76 cfg_aclconfctx_t *actx = *actxp;
77 *actxp = NULL;
78
79 if (isc_refcount_decrement(&actx->references) == 1) {
80 dns_acl_t *dacl, *next;
81 isc_refcount_destroy(&actx->references);
82 for (dacl = ISC_LIST_HEAD(actx->named_acl_cache);
83 dacl != NULL;
84 dacl = next)
85 {
86 next = ISC_LIST_NEXT(dacl, nextincache);
87 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(actx->named_acl_cache, dacl,
88 nextincache);
89 dns_acl_detach(&dacl);
90 }
91 isc_mem_putanddetach(&actx->mctx, actx, sizeof(*actx));
92 }
93}
94
95/*
96 * Find the definition of the named acl whose name is "name".
97 */
98static isc_result_t
99get_acl_def(const cfg_obj_t *cctx, const char *name, const cfg_obj_t **ret) {
100 isc_result_t result;
101 const cfg_obj_t *acls = NULL;
102 const cfg_listelt_t *elt;
103
104 result = cfg_map_get(cctx, "acl", &acls);
105 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
106 return (result);
107 for (elt = cfg_list_first(acls);
108 elt != NULL;
109 elt = cfg_list_next(elt)) {
110 const cfg_obj_t *acl = cfg_listelt_value(elt);
111 const char *aclname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(acl, "name"));
112 if (strcasecmp(aclname, name) == 0) {
113 if (ret != NULL) {
114 *ret = cfg_tuple_get(acl, "value");
115 }
116 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
117 }
118 }
119 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
120}
121
122static isc_result_t
123convert_named_acl(const cfg_obj_t *nameobj, const cfg_obj_t *cctx,
124 isc_log_t *lctx, cfg_aclconfctx_t *ctx,
125 isc_mem_t *mctx, unsigned int nest_level,
126 dns_acl_t **target)
127{
128 isc_result_t result;
129 const cfg_obj_t *cacl = NULL;
130 dns_acl_t *dacl;
131 dns_acl_t loop;
132 const char *aclname = cfg_obj_asstring(nameobj);
133
134 /* Look for an already-converted version. */
135 for (dacl = ISC_LIST_HEAD(ctx->named_acl_cache);
136 dacl != NULL;
137 dacl = ISC_LIST_NEXT(dacl, nextincache))
138 {
139 if (strcasecmp(aclname, dacl->name) == 0) {
140 if (ISC_MAGIC_VALID(dacl, LOOP_MAGIC)) {
141 cfg_obj_log(nameobj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
142 "acl loop detected: %s", aclname);
143 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
144 }
145 dns_acl_attach(dacl, target);
146 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
147 }
148 }
149 /* Not yet converted. Convert now. */
150 result = get_acl_def(cctx, aclname, &cacl);
151 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
152 cfg_obj_log(nameobj, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
153 "undefined ACL '%s'", aclname);
154 return (result);
155 }
156 /*
157 * Add a loop detection element.
158 */
159 memset(&loop, 0, sizeof(loop));
160 ISC_LINK_INIT(&loop, nextincache);
161 DE_CONST(aclname, loop.name);
162 loop.magic = LOOP_MAGIC;
163 ISC_LIST_APPEND(ctx->named_acl_cache, &loop, nextincache);
164 result = cfg_acl_fromconfig(cacl, cctx, lctx, ctx, mctx,
165 nest_level, &dacl);
166 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(ctx->named_acl_cache, &loop, nextincache);
167 loop.magic = 0;
168 loop.name = NULL;
169 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
170 return (result);
171 dacl->name = isc_mem_strdup(dacl->mctx, aclname);
172 if (dacl->name == NULL)
173 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
174 ISC_LIST_APPEND(ctx->named_acl_cache, dacl, nextincache);
175 dns_acl_attach(dacl, target);
176 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
177}

179static isc_result_t
180convert_keyname(const cfg_obj_t *keyobj, isc_log_t *lctx, isc_mem_t *mctx,
181 dns_name_t *dnsname)
182{
183 isc_result_t result;
184 isc_buffer_t buf;
185 dns_fixedname_t fixname;
186 unsigned int keylen;
187 const char *txtname = cfg_obj_asstring(keyobj);
188
189 keylen = strlen(txtname);
190 isc_buffer_constinit(&buf, txtname, keylen);
191 isc_buffer_add(&buf, keylen);
192 dns_fixedname_init(&fixname);
193 result = dns_name_fromtext(dns_fixedname_name(&fixname), &buf,
194 dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
195 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
196 cfg_obj_log(keyobj, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
197 "key name '%s' is not a valid domain name",
198 txtname);
199 return (result);
200 }
201 return (dns_name_dup(dns_fixedname_name(&fixname), mctx, dnsname));
202}

204/*
205 * Recursively pre-parse an ACL definition to find the total number
206 * of non-IP-prefix elements (localhost, localnets, key) in all nested
207 * ACLs, so that the parent will have enough space allocated for the
208 * elements table after all the nested ACLs have been merged in to the
209 * parent.
210 */
211static isc_result_t
212count_acl_elements(const cfg_obj_t *caml, const cfg_obj_t *cctx,
213 isc_log_t *lctx, cfg_aclconfctx_t *ctx, isc_mem_t *mctx,
214 uint32_t *count, bool *has_negative)
215{
216 const cfg_listelt_t *elt;
217 isc_result_t result;
218 uint32_t n = 0;
219
220 REQUIRE(count != NULL);
221
222 if (has_negative != NULL)
223 *has_negative = false;
224
225 for (elt = cfg_list_first(caml);
226 elt != NULL;
227 elt = cfg_list_next(elt)) {
228 const cfg_obj_t *ce = cfg_listelt_value(elt);
229
230 /* might be a negated element, in which case get the value. */
231 if (cfg_obj_istuple(ce)) {
232 const cfg_obj_t *negated =
233 cfg_tuple_get(ce, "negated");
234 if (! cfg_obj_isvoid(negated)) {
235 ce = negated;
236 if (has_negative != NULL)
237 *has_negative = true;
238 }
239 }
240
241 if (cfg_obj_istype(ce, &cfg_type_keyref)) {
242 n++;
243 } else if (cfg_obj_islist(ce)) {
244 bool negative;
245 uint32_t sub;
246 result = count_acl_elements(ce, cctx, lctx, ctx, mctx,
247 &sub, &negative);
248 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
249 return (result);
250 n += sub;
251 if (negative)
252 n++;
253#ifdef HAVE_GEOIP
254 } else if (cfg_obj_istuple(ce) &&
255 cfg_obj_isvoid(cfg_tuple_get(ce, "negated")))
256 {
257 n++;
258#endif /* HAVE_GEOIP */
259 } else if (cfg_obj_isstring(ce)) {
260 const char *name = cfg_obj_asstring(ce);
261 if (strcasecmp(name, "localhost") == 0 ||
262 strcasecmp(name, "localnets") == 0 ||
263 strcasecmp(name, "none") == 0)
264 {
265 n++;
266 } else if (strcasecmp(name, "any") != 0) {
267 dns_acl_t *inneracl = NULL;
268 /*
269 * Convert any named acls we reference now if
270 * they have not already been converted.
271 */
272 result = convert_named_acl(ce, cctx, lctx, ctx,
273 mctx, 0, &inneracl);
274 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
275 if (inneracl->has_negatives)
276 n++;
277 else
278 n += inneracl->length;
279 dns_acl_detach(&inneracl);
280 } else
281 return (result);
282 }
283 }
284 }
285
286 *count = n;
287 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
288}

290#ifdef HAVE_GEOIP
291static dns_geoip_subtype_t
292get_subtype(const cfg_obj_t *obj, isc_log_t *lctx,
293 dns_geoip_subtype_t subtype, const char *dbname)
294{
295 if (dbname == NULL)
296 return (subtype);
297
298 switch (subtype) {
299 case dns_geoip_countrycode:
300 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "city") == 0)
301 return (dns_geoip_city_countrycode);
302 else if (strcasecmp(dbname, "region") == 0)
303 return (dns_geoip_region_countrycode);
304 else if (strcasecmp(dbname, "country") == 0)
305 return (dns_geoip_country_code);
306 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
307 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
308 "country search: ignored");
309 return (subtype);
310 case dns_geoip_countrycode3:
311 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "city") == 0)
312 return (dns_geoip_city_countrycode3);
313 else if (strcasecmp(dbname, "country") == 0)
314 return (dns_geoip_country_code3);
315 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
316 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
317 "country search: ignored");
318 return (subtype);
319 case dns_geoip_countryname:
320 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "city") == 0)
321 return (dns_geoip_city_countryname);
322 else if (strcasecmp(dbname, "country") == 0)
323 return (dns_geoip_country_name);
324 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
325 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
326 "country search: ignored");
327 return (subtype);
328 case dns_geoip_region:
329 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "city") == 0)
330 return (dns_geoip_city_region);
331 else if (strcasecmp(dbname, "region") == 0)
332 return (dns_geoip_region_code);
333 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
334 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
335 "region search: ignored");
336 return (subtype);
337 case dns_geoip_regionname:
338 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "city") == 0)
339 return (dns_geoip_city_region);
340 else if (strcasecmp(dbname, "region") == 0)
341 return (dns_geoip_region_name);
342 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
343 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
344 "region search: ignored");
345 return (subtype);
346
347 /*
348 * Log a warning if the wrong database was specified
349 * on an unambiguous query
350 */
351 case dns_geoip_city_name:
352 case dns_geoip_city_postalcode:
353 case dns_geoip_city_metrocode:
354 case dns_geoip_city_areacode:
355 case dns_geoip_city_continentcode:
356 case dns_geoip_city_timezonecode:
357 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "city") != 0)
358 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
359 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
360 "a 'city'-only search type: ignoring");
361 return (subtype);
362 case dns_geoip_isp_name:
363 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "isp") != 0)
364 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
365 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
366 "an 'isp' search: ignoring");
367 return (subtype);
368 case dns_geoip_org_name:
369 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "org") != 0)
370 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
371 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
372 "an 'org' search: ignoring");
373 return (subtype);
374 case dns_geoip_as_asnum:
375 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "asnum") != 0)
376 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
377 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
378 "an 'asnum' search: ignoring");
379 return (subtype);
380 case dns_geoip_domain_name:
381 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "domain") != 0)
382 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
383 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
384 "a 'domain' search: ignoring");
385 return (subtype);
386 case dns_geoip_netspeed_id:
387 if (strcasecmp(dbname, "netspeed") != 0)
388 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
389 "invalid GeoIP DB specified for "
390 "a 'netspeed' search: ignoring");
391 return (subtype);
392 default:
393 INSIST(0);
394 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
395 }
396}

398static bool
399geoip_can_answer(dns_aclelement_t *elt, cfg_aclconfctx_t *ctx) {
400 if (ctx->geoip == NULL)
401 return (true);
402
403 switch (elt->geoip_elem.subtype) {
404 case dns_geoip_countrycode:
405 case dns_geoip_countrycode3:
406 case dns_geoip_countryname:
407 if (ctx->geoip->city_v4 != NULL ||
408 ctx->geoip->city_v6 != NULL ||
409 ctx->geoip->country_v4 != NULL ||
410 ctx->geoip->country_v6 != NULL ||
411 ctx->geoip->region != NULL)
412 return (true);
413 /* FALLTHROUGH */
414 case dns_geoip_region:
415 case dns_geoip_regionname:
416 if (ctx->geoip->city_v4 != NULL ||
417 ctx->geoip->city_v6 != NULL ||
418 ctx->geoip->region != NULL)
419 return (true);
420 /* FALLTHROUGH */
421 case dns_geoip_country_code:
422 case dns_geoip_country_code3:
423 case dns_geoip_country_name:
424 if (ctx->geoip->country_v4 != NULL ||
425 ctx->geoip->country_v6 != NULL)
426 return (true);
427 /* FALLTHROUGH */
428 case dns_geoip_region_countrycode:
429 case dns_geoip_region_code:
430 case dns_geoip_region_name:
431 if (ctx->geoip->region != NULL)
432 return (true);
433 /* FALLTHROUGH */
434 case dns_geoip_city_countrycode:
435 case dns_geoip_city_countrycode3:
436 case dns_geoip_city_countryname:
437 case dns_geoip_city_region:
438 case dns_geoip_city_regionname:
439 case dns_geoip_city_name:
440 case dns_geoip_city_postalcode:
441 case dns_geoip_city_metrocode:
442 case dns_geoip_city_areacode:
443 case dns_geoip_city_continentcode:
444 case dns_geoip_city_timezonecode:
445 if (ctx->geoip->city_v4 != NULL ||
446 ctx->geoip->city_v6 != NULL)
447 return (true);
448 /* FALLTHROUGH */
449 case dns_geoip_isp_name:
450 if (ctx->geoip->isp != NULL)
451 return (true);
452 /* FALLTHROUGH */
453 case dns_geoip_org_name:
454 if (ctx->geoip->org != NULL)
455 return (true);
456 /* FALLTHROUGH */
457 case dns_geoip_as_asnum:
458 if (ctx->geoip->as != NULL)
459 return (true);
460 /* FALLTHROUGH */
461 case dns_geoip_domain_name:
462 if (ctx->geoip->domain != NULL)
463 return (true);
464 /* FALLTHROUGH */
465 case dns_geoip_netspeed_id:
466 if (ctx->geoip->netspeed != NULL)
467 return (true);
468 }
469
470 return (false);
471}

473static isc_result_t
474parse_geoip_element(const cfg_obj_t *obj, isc_log_t *lctx,
475 cfg_aclconfctx_t *ctx, dns_aclelement_t *dep)
476{
477 const cfg_obj_t *ge;
478 const char *dbname = NULL;
479 const char *stype, *search;
480 dns_geoip_subtype_t subtype;
481 dns_aclelement_t de;
482 size_t len;
483
484 REQUIRE(dep != NULL);
485
486 de = *dep;
487
488 ge = cfg_tuple_get(obj, "db");
489 if (!cfg_obj_isvoid(ge))
490 dbname = cfg_obj_asstring(ge);
491
492 stype = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(obj, "subtype"));
493 search = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(obj, "search"));
494 len = strlen(search);
495
496 if (len == 0) {
497 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
498 "zero-length geoip search field");
499 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
500 }
501
502 if (strcasecmp(stype, "country") == 0 && len == 2) {
503 /* Two-letter country code */
504 subtype = dns_geoip_countrycode;
505 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
506 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
507 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "country") == 0 && len == 3) {
508 /* Three-letter country code */
509 subtype = dns_geoip_countrycode3;
510 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
511 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
512 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "country") == 0) {
513 /* Country name */
514 subtype = dns_geoip_countryname;
515 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
516 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
517 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "region") == 0 && len == 2) {
518 /* Two-letter region code */
519 subtype = dns_geoip_region;
520 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
521 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
522 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "region") == 0) {
523 /* Region name */
524 subtype = dns_geoip_regionname;
525 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
526 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
527 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "city") == 0) {
528 /* City name */
529 subtype = dns_geoip_city_name;
530 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
531 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
532 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "postal") == 0 ||
533 strcasecmp(stype, "postalcode") == 0)
534 {
535 if (len < 7) {
536 subtype = dns_geoip_city_postalcode;
537 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
538 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
539 } else {
540 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
541 "geoiop postal code (%s) too long",
542 search);
543 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
544 }
545 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "metro") == 0 ||
546 strcasecmp(stype, "metrocode") == 0)
547 {
548 subtype = dns_geoip_city_metrocode;
549 de.geoip_elem.as_int = atoi(search);
550 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "area") == 0 ||
551 strcasecmp(stype, "areacode") == 0)
552 {
553 subtype = dns_geoip_city_areacode;
554 de.geoip_elem.as_int = atoi(search);
555 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "tz") == 0 ||
556 strcasecmp(stype, "timezone") == 0)
557 {
558 subtype = dns_geoip_city_timezonecode;
559 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
560 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
561 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "continent") == 0 && len == 2) {
562 /* Two-letter continent code */
563 subtype = dns_geoip_city_continentcode;
564 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
565 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
566 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "continent") == 0) {
567 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
568 "geoiop continent code (%s) too long", search);
569 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
570 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "isp") == 0) {
571 subtype = dns_geoip_isp_name;
572 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
573 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
574 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "asnum") == 0) {
575 subtype = dns_geoip_as_asnum;
576 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
577 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
578 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "org") == 0) {
579 subtype = dns_geoip_org_name;
580 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
581 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
582 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "domain") == 0) {
583 subtype = dns_geoip_domain_name;
584 strlcpy(de.geoip_elem.as_string, search,
585 sizeof(de.geoip_elem.as_string));
586 } else if (strcasecmp(stype, "netspeed") == 0) {
587 subtype = dns_geoip_netspeed_id;
588 de.geoip_elem.as_int = atoi(search);
589 } else {
590 INSIST(0);
591 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
592 }
593
594 de.geoip_elem.subtype = get_subtype(obj, lctx, subtype, dbname);
595
596 if (! geoip_can_answer(&de, ctx)) {
597 cfg_obj_log(obj, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
598 "no GeoIP database installed which can answer "
599 "queries of type '%s'", stype);
600 return (ISC_R_FAILURE);
601 }
602
603 *dep = de;
604
605 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
606}
607#endif

609isc_result_t
610cfg_acl_fromconfig(const cfg_obj_t *caml, const cfg_obj_t *cctx,
611 isc_log_t *lctx, cfg_aclconfctx_t *ctx,
612 isc_mem_t *mctx, unsigned int nest_level,
613 dns_acl_t **target)
614{
615 return (cfg_acl_fromconfig2(caml, cctx, lctx, ctx, mctx,
616 nest_level, 0, target));
617}
618
619isc_result_t
620cfg_acl_fromconfig2(const cfg_obj_t *caml, const cfg_obj_t *cctx,
621 isc_log_t *lctx, cfg_aclconfctx_t *ctx,
622 isc_mem_t *mctx, unsigned int nest_level,
623 uint16_t family, dns_acl_t **target)
624{
625 isc_result_t result;
626 dns_acl_t *dacl = NULL, *inneracl = NULL;
627 dns_aclelement_t *de;
628 const cfg_listelt_t *elt;
629 dns_iptable_t *iptab;
630 int new_nest_level = 0;
631 bool setpos;
632
633 if (nest_level != 0)
634 new_nest_level = nest_level - 1;
635
636 REQUIRE(target != NULL);
637 REQUIRE(*target == NULL || DNS_ACL_VALID(*target));
638
639 if (*target != NULL) {
640 /*
641 * If target already points to an ACL, then we're being
642 * called recursively to configure a nested ACL. The
643 * nested ACL's contents should just be absorbed into its
644 * parent ACL.
645 */
646 dns_acl_attach(*target, &dacl);
647 dns_acl_detach(target);
648 } else {
649 /*
650 * Need to allocate a new ACL structure. Count the items
651 * in the ACL definition that will require space in the
652 * elements table. (Note that if nest_level is nonzero,
653 * *everything* goes in the elements table.)
654 */
655 uint32_t nelem;
656
657 if (nest_level == 0) {
658 result = count_acl_elements(caml, cctx, lctx, ctx,
659 mctx, &nelem, NULL);
660 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
661 return (result);
662 } else
663 nelem = cfg_list_length(caml, false);
664
665 result = dns_acl_create(mctx, nelem, &dacl);
666 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
667 return (result);
668 }
669
670 de = dacl->elements;
671 for (elt = cfg_list_first(caml);
672 elt != NULL;
673 elt = cfg_list_next(elt)) {
674 const cfg_obj_t *ce = cfg_listelt_value(elt);
675 bool neg = false;
676
677 INSIST(dacl->length <= dacl->alloc);
678
679 if (cfg_obj_istuple(ce)) {
680 /* Might be a negated element */
681 const cfg_obj_t *negated =
682 cfg_tuple_get(ce, "negated");
683 if (! cfg_obj_isvoid(negated)) {
684 neg = true;
685 dacl->has_negatives = true;
686 ce = negated;
687 }
688 }
689
690 /*
691 * If nest_level is nonzero, then every element is
692 * to be stored as a separate, nested ACL rather than
693 * merged into the main iptable.
694 */
695 iptab = dacl->iptable;
696
697 if (nest_level != 0) {
698 result = dns_acl_create(mctx,
699 cfg_list_length(ce, false),
700 &de->nestedacl);
701 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
702 goto cleanup;
703 iptab = de->nestedacl->iptable;
704 }
705
706 if (cfg_obj_isnetprefix(ce)) {
707 /* Network prefix */
708 isc_netaddr_t addr;
709 unsigned int bitlen;
710
711 cfg_obj_asnetprefix(ce, &addr, &bitlen);
712 if (family != 0 && family != addr.family) {
713 char buf[ISC_NETADDR_FORMATSIZE + 1];
714 isc_netaddr_format(&addr, buf, sizeof(buf));
715 cfg_obj_log(ce, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
716 "'%s': incorrect address family; "
717 "ignoring", buf);
718 if (nest_level != 0)
719 dns_acl_detach(&de->nestedacl);
720 continue;
721 }
722 result = isc_netaddr_prefixok(&addr, bitlen);
723 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
724 char buf[ISC_NETADDR_FORMATSIZE + 1];
725 isc_netaddr_format(&addr, buf, sizeof(buf));
726 cfg_obj_log(ce, lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
727 "'%s/%u': address/prefix length "
728 "mismatch", buf, bitlen);
729 goto cleanup;
730 }
731
732 /*
733 * If nesting ACLs (nest_level != 0), we negate
734 * the nestedacl element, not the iptable entry.
735 */
736 setpos = (nest_level != 0 || !neg);
737 result = dns_iptable_addprefix(iptab, &addr, bitlen,
738 setpos);
739 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
740 goto cleanup;
741
742 if (nest_level > 0) {
743 INSIST(dacl->length < dacl->alloc);
744 de->type = dns_aclelementtype_nestedacl;
745 de->negative = neg;
746 } else
747 continue;
748 } else if (cfg_obj_islist(ce)) {
749 /*
750 * If we're nesting ACLs, put the nested
751 * ACL onto the elements list; otherwise
752 * merge it into *this* ACL. We nest ACLs
753 * in two cases: 1) sortlist, 2) if the
754 * nested ACL contains negated members.
755 */
756 if (inneracl != NULL)
757 dns_acl_detach(&inneracl);
758 result = cfg_acl_fromconfig(ce, cctx, lctx,
759 ctx, mctx, new_nest_level,
760 &inneracl);
761 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
762 goto cleanup;
763nested_acl:
764 if (nest_level > 0 || inneracl->has_negatives) {
765 INSIST(dacl->length < dacl->alloc);
766 de->type = dns_aclelementtype_nestedacl;
767 de->negative = neg;
768 if (de->nestedacl != NULL)
769 dns_acl_detach(&de->nestedacl);
770 dns_acl_attach(inneracl,
771 &de->nestedacl);
772 dns_acl_detach(&inneracl);
773 /* Fall through. */
774 } else {
775 INSIST(dacl->length + inneracl->length
776 <= dacl->alloc);
777 dns_acl_merge(dacl, inneracl,
778 !neg);
779 de += inneracl->length; /* elements added */
780 dns_acl_detach(&inneracl);
781 INSIST(dacl->length <= dacl->alloc);
782 continue;
783 }
784 } else if (cfg_obj_istype(ce, &cfg_type_keyref)) {
785 /* Key name. */
786 INSIST(dacl->length < dacl->alloc);
787 de->type = dns_aclelementtype_keyname;
788 de->negative = neg;
789 dns_name_init(&de->keyname, NULL);
790 result = convert_keyname(ce, lctx, mctx,
791 &de->keyname);
792 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
793 goto cleanup;
794#ifdef HAVE_GEOIP
795 } else if (cfg_obj_istuple(ce) &&
796 cfg_obj_isvoid(cfg_tuple_get(ce, "negated")))
797 {
798 INSIST(dacl->length < dacl->alloc);
799 result = parse_geoip_element(ce, lctx, ctx, de);
800 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
801 goto cleanup;
802 de->type = dns_aclelementtype_geoip;
803 de->negative = neg;
804#endif /* HAVE_GEOIP */
805 } else if (cfg_obj_isstring(ce)) {
806 /* ACL name. */
807 const char *name = cfg_obj_asstring(ce);
808 if (strcasecmp(name, "any") == 0) {
809 /* Iptable entry with zero bit length. */
810 setpos = (nest_level != 0 || !neg);
811 result = dns_iptable_addprefix(iptab, NULL, 0,
812 setpos);
813 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
814 goto cleanup;
815
816 if (nest_level != 0) {
817 INSIST(dacl->length < dacl->alloc);
818 de->type = dns_aclelementtype_nestedacl;
819 de->negative = neg;
820 } else
821 continue;
822 } else if (strcasecmp(name, "none") == 0) {
823 /* none == !any */
824 /*
825 * We don't unconditional set
826 * dacl->has_negatives and
827 * de->negative to true so we can handle
828 * "!none;".
829 */
830 setpos = (nest_level != 0 || neg);
831 result = dns_iptable_addprefix(iptab, NULL, 0,
832 setpos);
833 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
834 goto cleanup;
835
836 if (!neg)
837 dacl->has_negatives = !neg;
838
839 if (nest_level != 0) {
840 INSIST(dacl->length < dacl->alloc);
841 de->type = dns_aclelementtype_nestedacl;
842 de->negative = !neg;
843 } else
844 continue;
845 } else if (strcasecmp(name, "localhost") == 0) {
846 INSIST(dacl->length < dacl->alloc);
847 de->type = dns_aclelementtype_localhost;
848 de->negative = neg;
849 } else if (strcasecmp(name, "localnets") == 0) {
850 INSIST(dacl->length < dacl->alloc);
851 de->type = dns_aclelementtype_localnets;
852 de->negative = neg;
853 } else {
854 if (inneracl != NULL)
855 dns_acl_detach(&inneracl);
856 /*
857 * This call should just find the cached
858 * of the named acl.
859 */
860 result = convert_named_acl(ce, cctx, lctx, ctx,
861 mctx, new_nest_level,
862 &inneracl);
863 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
864 goto cleanup;
865
866 goto nested_acl;
867 }
868 } else {
869 cfg_obj_log(ce, lctx, ISC_LOG_WARNING,
870 "address match list contains "
871 "unsupported element type");
872 result = ISC_R_FAILURE;
873 goto cleanup;
874 }
875
876 /*
877 * This should only be reached for localhost, localnets
878 * and keyname elements, and nested ACLs if nest_level is
879 * nonzero (i.e., in sortlists).
880 */
881 if (de->nestedacl != NULL &&
882 de->type != dns_aclelementtype_nestedacl)
883 dns_acl_detach(&de->nestedacl);
884
885 dacl->node_count++;
886 de->node_num = dacl->node_count;
887
888 dacl->length++;
889 de++;
890 INSIST(dacl->length <= dacl->alloc);
891 }
892
893 dns_acl_attach(dacl, target);
894 result = ISC_R_SUCCESS;
895
896 cleanup:
897 if (inneracl != NULL)
898 dns_acl_detach(&inneracl);
899 dns_acl_detach(&dacl);
900 return (result);
901}
